3D%5C%220a0c541d-70be-4095-8cec-2473f8f18dce%5C%22%3EMy%20teens%20can%20wear%20what%20they%20want%2C%20within%20reason%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20kid%20has%20their%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsophie-strauss-stylist-regular-people-style-tips-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esense%20of%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I'm%20fine%20with%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20teens%20went%20through%20a%20phase%20of%20wearing%20all%20black.%20Another%20prefers%20to%20wear%20the%20same%20hoodie%20almost%20every%20day.%20One%20loves%20jeans%2C%20while%20one%20of%20my%20kids%20loathes%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20draw%20the%20line%20in%20certain%20situations%2C%20but%20I%20use%20these%20opportunities%20%E2%80%94%20church%2C%20a%20funeral%2C%20a%20wedding%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-linkedin-tiktok-job-interview-outfits-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20teach%20my%20kids%20to%20%26quot%3Bread%20the%20room.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20big%20proponent%20of%20dressing%20for%20comfort.%20Even%20on%20special%20occasions%2C%20like%20when%20we%20recently%20attended%20my%20dear%20aunt's%20funeral%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20my%20kids%20have%20appropriate%20attire%20that%20still%20meets%20their%20sensory%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271692f53-55ec-4979-9db8-999390484ccb%5C%22%3EMy%20teens%20can%20choose%20their%20own%20extracurricular%20activities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20not%20trying%20to%20live%20out%20our%20own%20childhood%20dreams%20or%20past%20preferences%20through%20our%20teens.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20grew%20up%20playing%20golf%2C%20playing%20in%20the%20school%20band%2C%20and%20earning%20the%20rank%20of%20Eagle%20Scout.%20None%20of%20our%20kids%20are%20in%20or%20have%20been%20in%20Scouts%20or%20golf%2C%20though%20one%20did%20join%20the%20school%20band%20for%20a%20short%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20our%20kids%20to%20pursue%20their%20interests%20and%20build%20their%20own%20skill%20sets.%20Right%20now%2C%20I%20have%20one%20teen%20who%20likes%20art%20and%20Color%20Guard%2C%20another%20who%20plays%20basketball%2C%20and%20another%20who%20wrestles.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20the%20activity%20is%20doable%20for%20our%20large%20family%2C%20financially%20and%20physically%2C%20we%20allow%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225eedcca1-0144-4f92-935f-70b3fa05a908%5C%22%3EMy%20teens%20can%20choose%20their%20own%20media%20consumption%2C%20with%20a%20few%20exceptions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20the%20parent%20who%20micromanages%20the%20movies%2C%20music%2C%20podcasts%2C%20audiobooks%2C%20or%20TV%20shows%20that%20my%20teens%20choose%20to%20consume.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we've%20had%20plenty%20of%20conversations%20about%20%26quot%3Bgarbage%20in%2C%20garbage%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20listening%20to%20their%20own%20brain%20and%20body%20cues%2C%20and%20remembering%20they%20have%20a%20younger%20sister%20who%20is%20observing%20what%20her%20older%20siblings%20choose%20to%20do%20or%20not%20do%20%E2%80%94%20in%20all%20aspects%2C%20not%20just%20with%20media%20choices.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20have%20fairly%20strict%20phone%20rules%20for%20our%20kids%2C%20including%20no%20social%20media%2C%20as%20we%20are%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20detrimental%20effects%20of%20such%20use.%20I%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20develop%20their%20own%20preferences%20and%20honor%20their%20tastes%2C%20not%20just%20lock%20in%20to%20whatever%20we%20prefer%20or%20what%20their%20peers%20think%20is%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d1f8a87-7843-476e-a903-77becef278b3%5C%22%3EMy%20teens%20choose%20their%20friends%20and%20who%20they%20date%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20give%20our%20teens%20the%20freedom%20to%20select%20their%20friends%20and%20who%20they%20date.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20also%20believe%20in%20being%20good%20role%20models%20for%20what%20a%20healthy%2C%20balanced%20friendship%20and%20dating%20relationship%20looks%20like.%20We%20don't%20hesitate%20to%20point%20out%20red%20flags.%20That%20said%2C%20we%20also%20know%20that%20the%20teen%20years%20are%20a%20time%20of%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20live%20and%20learn.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20to%20walk%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20giving%20freedom%2C%20offering%20guidance%2C%20and%20stepping%20in%2C%20only%20when%20absolutely%20necessary.%20We%20also%20have%20to%20refrain%20from%20saying%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20you%20so%26quot%3B%20when%20a%20relationship%20goes%20awry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-teens-pick-your-battles-what-not-to-fight-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774728481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69bb07e2d387710cb9e4602e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-teens-pick-your-battles-what-not-to-fight-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Parenting%20teens%20can%20feel%20like%20constant%20conflict.%20I've%20learned%20to%20pick%20my%20battles%20%E2%80%94%20here's%20what%20I%20don't%20argue%20about.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Rachel%20Garlinghouse)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-teens-pick-your-battles-what-not-to-fight-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World%20of%20%E2%80%98Frozen%E2%80%99%20Debuts%20at%20Disneyland%20Paris%3A%20How%20Walt%20Disney%20Imagineers%20Brought%20Olaf%20and%20Elsa%E2%80%99s%20Ice%20Palace%20to%20Life%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774728208000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236701490%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Visitors%20of%20Disneyland%20Paris%20finally%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20experience%20A