025%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20my%20first%20men's%20national%20championship%20team%20in%201998%20and%20then%20again%20in%202001.%20I've%20been%20to%20the%20last%2021%20out%20of%2023%20national%20championships%3B%20I%20won%20two%20of%20them.%20I've%20also%20been%20in%20Olympic%20trials.%20But%20the%202026%20Olympics%20were%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabandoned-olympic-venues-current-day-pictures-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20Olympics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20the%20alternate%20on%20the%20US%20men's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusa-curling-wrong-gold-medals-winter-olympics-ceremony-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecurling%20team%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20the%20oldest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-in-sports-historic-firsts-female-athletes-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20Olympian%3C%2Fa%3E%20ever%20to%20compete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d37cfdbc-1654-4941-b9f8-61f9da71e3ad%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20unusual%20to%20have%20a%20day%20job%20as%20an%20Olympian%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20lawyer%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-psychologist-the-race-is-the-easiest-part-of-the-olympics-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompetitive%20curler%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20global%20athletes%20are%20paid%20by%20their%20governments%20to%20compete%20in%20curling%2C%20bobsledding%2C%20etc.%20Their%20only%20job%20is%20to%20train%20for%20the%20World%20Championships%2C%20which%20happen%20every%20year%2C%20and%20the%20Olympics%2C%20which%20occur%20every%20four%20years.%20They%20might%20get%20a%20salary%2C%20have%20their%20expenses%20paid%2C%20and%20get%20to%20keep%20any%20winnings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20that's%20not%20how%20it%20works.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20disadvantages%20of%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-olympic-athletes-broke-how-they-make-money-tokyo-2020-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20athlete%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20train%20full-time.%20We%20do%20get%20a%20small%20stipend%2C%20but%20many%20US%20athletes%20have%20side%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22702930ae-61fa-40c9-9171-aad78d8e5dc4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20to%20work%20training%20into%20my%20day%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20schedule%20is%20complicated.%20On%20a%20week%20when%20I%20am%20not%20preparing%20for%20a%20competition%2C%20I'm%20at%20the%20gym%20four%20days%20a%20week%2C%20leaving%20my%20house%20at%205%3A15%20a.m.%20to%20drive%2030%20miles%20to%20the%20training%20facility.%20I'm%20there%20at%206%20a.m.%20and%20train%20until%207%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20then%20jump%20in%20the%20shower%20and%20rush%20to%20work.%20I%20work%20from%208%20a.m.%20to%206%20p.m.%2C%20sometimes%20longer.%20I%20go%20home%20and%20sometimes%20work%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20play%20in%20a%20Tuesday%20night%20league%20during%20the%20season.%20I%20also%20%26quot%3Bthrow%20rocks%2C%26quot%3B%20what%20we%20call%20practice%20in%20curling%2C%20several%20nights%20a%20week.%20I'll%20often%20throw%20on%20Saturdays%20and%20Sundays%2C%20two%20to%20four%20hours%20a%20day.%20Every%20waking%20moment%20between%20those%20sessions%2C%20I'm%20working%2C%20including%20the%20weekends%2C%20to%20get%20caught%20up%20at%20my%20day%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20on%20the%20road%2C%20I'm%20still%20putting%20in%2040%20hours%20or%20more%20of%20work.%20It's%20not%20easy.%20It's%20not%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20fun%2C%20but%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpointone-series-a-funding-lawyers-billable-hour-timekeeping-ai-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20don't%20sleep%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurling%20at%20this%20level%20is%20a%20major%20commitment.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20sacrifice%2C%20including%20from%20my%20wife%2C%20who%20stayed%20home%20because%20I%20wasn't%20there%20and%20who%20had%20to%20do%20more%20of%20the%20stuff%20with%20the%20kids%2C%20who%20are%2021%20and%2024%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22123eb845-6807-4b49-8e49-d802d5d4fc0d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhile%20the%20Olympics%20might%20be%20over%2C%20I'm%20still%20curling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20playing%20in%20the%20senior%20World%20Championship%20in%20April.%20I%20am%20sure%20I%20am%20the%20only%20guy%20to%20ever%20go%20to%20the%20senior%20World%20Championship%20and%20the%20Olympics%20in%20the%20same%20year.%20We%20are%20hoping%20to%20win%20gold%20this%20year.%20I%20also%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20charity%20curling%2C%20such%20as%20for%20the%20Lupus%20Foundation.%20People%20raise%20money%20to%20play%20with%20me%20as%20their%20skip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20already%20been%20some%20interest%20in%20me%20playing%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-switzerland-aims-host-cheapest-winter-olympics-budget-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E2030%20Olympics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20yes.%20It's%20been%20a%20huge%20commitment%20for%2025%20years.%20Even%20though%20I'd%20be%20in%20an%20alternate%20role%20again%20in%202030%2C%20I'm%20still%20required%20to%20do%20all%20the%20practices%20and%20attend%20everything.%20These%20other%20curlers%20are%20in%20their%2020s%3B%20I'm%20twice%20their%20age.%20I%20haven't%20fully%20decided.%20I'm%20still%20throwing%20well%20enough%20to%20keep%20playing%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20good%20about%20playing%20at%20this%20level.%20But%20it%20is%20harder%20to%20get%20up%20in%20the%20morning%20with%20my%20knees%20cracking%20all%20the%20time.%20I%20also%20think%20of%20how%20nice%20it%20would%20be%20to%20go%20to%20Mexico%20in%20the%20winter%20instead%20of%20Calgary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%