.com%2Fsenate-reaches-deal-fund-tsa-dhs-end-shutdown-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eend%20the%20partial%20government%20shutdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fund%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DHS%20said%20its%20agents%20could%20start%20seeing%20paychecks%20again%20as%20soon%20as%20Monday%2C%20but%20if%20you%20thought%20that%20would%20mean%20shorter%20airport%20security%20lines%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20pack%20a%20snack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airline%20industry%20is%20facing%20an%20assembly%20of%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20war%2C%20rising%20costs%2C%20staffing%20shortages%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20making%20flying%20more%20expensive%20and%20stressful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222c9e41a4-4e95-4c76-936f-e9774444ecbe%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStaffing%20Shortages%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20funding%20lapse%20had%20forced%20TSA%20officers%2C%20who%20make%20a%20starting%20salary%20of%20about%20%2440%2C000%20and%20often%20live%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20to%20go%20without%20wages%20for%20weeks.%20Hundreds%20of%20them%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20full%20paychecks%20to%20come%20soon%2C%20the%20TSA%20will%20need%20to%20address%20this%20staffing%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHa%20Nguyen%20McNeill%2C%20the%20agency's%20deputy%20administrator%2C%20said%20almost%20500%20officers%20have%20quit%20since%20the%20partial%20shutdown%20began%20in%20mid-February.%20More%20than%201%2C000%20TSA%20agents%20also%20quit%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-vote-government-reopened-longest-shutdown-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E43-day%20government%20shutdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20late%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TSA%20employs%20about%2050%2C000%20officers%2C%20but%20it%20takes%204%20to%206%20months%20to%20complete%20training.%20That%20means%20those%20long%20lines%20might%20linger%20a%20while%20longer.%20It's%20possible%20those%20open%20roles%20may%20not%20be%20filled%20in%20time%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-staffing-crisis-long-lines-world-cup-june-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFIFA%20World%20Cup%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20dire%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20McNeill%20told%20lawmakers%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20facing%20a%20potential%20perfect%20storm%20of%20severe%20staffing%20shortages%20and%20an%20influx%20of%20millions%20of%20passengers%20at%20our%20airports.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20Stahl%2C%20the%20TSA%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20also%20addressed%20staffing%20lapses%20on%20Wednesday.%20He%20said%20the%20situation%20will%20%26quot%3Bget%20worse%20before%20it%20gets%20better%26quot%3B%20despite%20Trump's%20executive%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20knock-on%20ramifications%20of%20attrition%20when%20the%20shutdown%20ends%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahl%20told%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hill%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20TV%20news%20program%20on%20NewsNation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20recruiting%20pipeline%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bchallenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFolks%20that%20are%20possibly%20in%20the%20pipeline%20or%20they're%20considering%20going%20and%20joining%20the%20workforce%20will%20be%20dissuaded%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20job%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahl%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e9834ee-7f9f-429e-95a9-833210e947ce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlying%20is%20getting%20pricier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJet%20fuel%20costs%20are%20skyrocketing%20due%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Israel's%20war%20on%20Iran%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20add%20to%20the%20already%20elevated%20cost%20of%20flying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrices%20have%20surged%20to%20about%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-air-travel-passengers-airports-senate-deal-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24200%20a%20barrel%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20February%2C%20far%20surpassing%20the%20earlier%20%24100%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20some%20airlines%20are%20relying%20on%20consumers%20to%20cover%20the%20additional%20costs.%20Qantas%20Airways%2C%20Air%20India%2C%20Thai%20Air%2C%20and%20other%20airlines%20have%20already%20alerted%20flyers%20that%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-raise-prices-cancel-flights-due-to-fuel-costs-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraising%20ticket%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20military%20conflict%20has%20effectively%20shut%20down%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%2C%20a%20waterway%20near%20Iran's%20coast%20through%20which%2020%25%20of%20the%20world's%20oil%20supply%20and%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20typically%20pass.%20Other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-fire-key-uae-oil-hub-after-intercepted-drone-attack-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20oil%20hubs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20a%20key%20port%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20have%20sustained%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20has%20also%20forced%20some%20countries%20to%20close%20their%20airspace%2C%20forcing%20airlines%20to%20reroute%20flights%20and%20find%20alternative%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ec69ab3-1772-46f1-a504-c4901baa7332%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMounting%20anxiety%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20is%20good%20for%20the%20airline%20industry.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESome%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20anxious%20about%20air%20travel%2C%20which%20could%20make%20them%20think%20twice%20about%20purchasing%20costly%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20Ipsos%20survey%20conducted%20in%20February%2C%20almost%20half%20of%20respondents%20said%20they're%20%26quot%3Blosing%20confidence%20in%20the%20safety%20of%20air%20travel.%26quot%3B%20Respondents%20with%20household%20incomes%20over%20%24125%2C000%20had%20even%20less%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20likely%20a%20worrying%20stat%20for%20the%20travel%20industry%20as%20the%20high%20earners%20are%20much%20more%20frequent%20fliers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20global%20market%20research%20firm%20wrote%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%2030%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20felt%20%26quot%3Bconfident%20in%20the%20safety%20of%20air%20travel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20doesn't%20specify%20a%20reason.%20However%2C%20there%20could%20be%20several%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20war's%20impact%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-chaos-iran-war-air-travel-ticket-price-cancellation-diversion-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einternational%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rising%20ticket%20prices%20during%20a%20time%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-war-economic-impact-oil-prices-inflation-supply-el-erian-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fallout%20from%20staff%20shortages%2C%20or%20a%20string%20of%20recent%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20a%20passenger%20jet%20collided%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-subsidiary-plane-psa-crashes-potomac-river-dc-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlack%20Hawk%20helicopter%3C%2Fa%3E%20near%20the%20Reagan%20Washington%20National%20Airport.%20Sixty-seven%20people%20died.%20And%20this%20week%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faudio-captures-final-moments-before-plane-truck-collision-at-laguardia-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAir%20Canada%20passenger%20plane%3C%2Fa%3E%20crashed%20into%20a%20fire%20truck%2C%20killing%20two%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairport-lines-tsa-travel-disruption-security-rising-ticket-prices-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insi