viewed%20for%20Business%20Insider's%20CMO%20Insider%20video%20series.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZoom's%20ad%20campaign%20with%20former%20SNL%20star%20Bowen%20Yang%20was%20created%20by%20SNL's%20Colin%20Jost%20and%20his%20production%20agency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStorin%20said%20Zoom's%20AI%20Companion%20tool%20helps%20her%20turn%20her%20daily%20conversations%20into%20strategic%20insight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Kimberly%20Storin%20joined%20Zoom%20as%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%20in%20April%202025%2C%20she%20did%20her%20own%20research%20to%20learn%20what%20users%20thought%20of%20the%20brand.%20Storin%20said%20she%20discovered%20a%20strong%20affinity%20for%20Zoom%20compared%20to%20its%20competitors.%20Still%2C%20many%20of%20the%20platform's%20features%20are%20not%20well%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20insight%20inspired%20a%20campaign%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.zoom.com%2Fzoom-ahead-brand-campaign%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommercial%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20%26quot%3BZoom%20Ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20created%20by%20Saturday%20Night%20Live's%20Colin%20Jost's%20production%20company%2C%20and%20featuring%20former%20SNL%20cast%20member%20Bowen%20Yang.%20In%20the%20spot%2C%20Yang%20plays%20a%20tyrannical%20head%20of%20IT%20who%20is%20powerless%20to%20prevent%20employees%20from%20declaring%20their%20love%20of%20Zoom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZoom%20extended%20the%20theme%20of%20worker%20empowerment%20with%20an%20in-person%20activation%3A%20a%20Hard%20Stop%20Burger%20Shop%20pop-up%20in%20New%20York%20City%20on%20March%2026-27.%20The%20idea%20was%20based%20on%20research%20the%20company%20conducted%20with%20Morning%20Consult%20that%20showed%20workers%20are%20skipping%20breaks%20or%20eating%20lunch%20at%20their%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20interview%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20Storin%20about%20the%20strategy%20behind%20the%20campaign%20and%20why%20she's%20such%20a%20fan%20of%20the%20company's%20AI%20Companion%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2Ft0VaLyUs-puACk8ZV.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20transcript%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20challenge%20Zoom%20has%20is%20that%20ultimately%2C%20we%20are%20a%20ubiquitous%20brand.%20We%20have%2099%25%20brand%20awareness%2C%20which%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20double-edged%20sword.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20people%20don't%20realize%20is%20the%20breadth%20and%20depth%20of%20our%20portfolio.%20They%20don't%20realize%20we%20have%20a%20customer%20support%20platform%2C%20a%20marketing%20platform%20with%20events%20and%20webinars%2C%20a%20recruiting%20platform%2C%20or%20a%20sales%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20started%20at%20Zoom%2C%20I%20talked%20to%20about%2050%20of%20the%20company's%20customers.%20Those%20customers%20told%20me%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20about%20their%20affinity%20for%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20went%20down%20this%20rabbit%20hole%20of%20Reddit%20and%20social%20media%2C%20and%20I%20kept%20seeing%20this%20theme%20in%20the%20conversations%20I%20didn't%20see%20with%20any%20of%20our%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20really%20anchored%20in%20this%20preference%20for%20the%20Zoom%20platform%2C%20the%20simplicity%2C%20the%20ease%20of%20use%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20Zoom%20just%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20genesis%2C%20the%20nugget%20that%20really%20inspired%20our%20campaign.%20We%20wanted%20to%20start%20a%20revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20chief%20information%20officer%20ask%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20trying%20to%20encourage%20shadow%20IT%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we're%20actually%20trying%20to%20do%20the%20opposite.%26quot%3B%20We're%20trying%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20come%20out%20of%20the%20shadows%20and%20share%20their%20love%20for%20the%20platform%20in%20the%20ways%20that%20they're%20sharing%20it%20on%20Reddit%2C%20social%20media%2C%20and%20in%20our%20customer%20satisfaction%20scores%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20want%20them%20to%20tell%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7a4ac0c-77f9-4278-a5e0-df07cd541746%5C%22%3EColin%20Jost%20was%20able%20to%20find%20the%20right%20humorous%20tone%20for%20the%20ad%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHumor%20is%20hard%20for%20a%20brand.%20And%20to%20get%20humor%20right%20really%20requires%20people%20who%20understand%20comedy%2C%20who%20understand%20how%20humor%20can%20play%20a%20role%20in%20communication%2C%20and%20who%20can%20explain%20something%20in%20a%20way%20that%20a%20straight-faced%20ad%20really%20can't.%20And%20so%2C%20of%20course%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20tap%20into%20the%20best%20of%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20in%20suit%20standing%20on%20desk%20with%20another%20man%20in%20a%20suit%20in%20front%20of%20him%20pointing%20in%20the%20air.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c58ba1399d535730953441%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBowen%20Yang%20stars%20in%20Zoom's%20campaign%3Cp%3ENo%20Notes%20Productions%20for%20Zoom%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EColin%20Jost%20really%20reflects%20the%20cultural%20zeitgeist%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways.%20Every%20single%20week%2C%20he's%20writing%20comedy%20that%20resonates%20and%20stands%20up%20to%20the%20news%20of%20the%20week.%20We%20felt%20that%20with%20Zoom%20being%20such%20a%20cultural%20brand%20and%20part%20of%20so%20many%20people's%20cultural%20experience%2C%20having%20somebody%20who%20understands%20humor%20in%20that%20way%20would%20really%20help%20elevate%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20brought%20in%20Colin%20and%20his%20team%20from%20his%20agency%20called%20No%20Notes%20Productions.%20They%20helped%20us%20understand%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20ways%20that%20we%20could%20leverage%20humor%20and%20heart%20to%20bring%20this%20product%20to%20life.%20Some%20of%20it%20was%20outrageous.%20Some%20of%20it%20was%20formulaic%20in%20terms%20of%20leveraging%20a%20celebrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20we%20ended%20up%20landing%2C%20and%20what%20ended%20up%20testing%20really%20well%20with%20our%20customers%2C%20was%20this%20idea%20that%20we%20call%20%26quot%3BDead%20Poets%20Society%26quot%3B%20meets%20%26quot%3BSeverance.%26quot%3B%20It%20just%20really%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8ea8b84-5ec9-46ee-9904-3c2e0e99d26f%5C%22%3EThe%20AI%20Companion%20helps%20connect%20daily%20conversations%20to%20strategy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20how%20many%20folks%20are%20familiar%20with%20our%20AI%20Companion%2C%20but%20that%20is%20absolutely%20my%20favorite%20tool.%20The%20reason%20I%20love%20it%20so%20much%20is%20because%20I%20believe%20that%20so%20much%20of%20the%20data%20and%20the%20information%20that%20matters%20to%20us%20as%20executives%20happens%20in%20those%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20traditional%20LLM%20like%20ChatGPT%20or%20Claude%2C%20which%20is%20really%20focused%20on%20external%20data%2C%20the%20beauty%20of%20Zoom%20AI%20Companion%20is%20that%20you%20can%20pull%20in%20all%20your%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20click%20of%20a%20button%2C%20you%20can%20build%20an%20agent%20that%20effectively%20taps%20into%20all%20of%20the%20conversations%20that%20you've%20had%20and%20is%20able%20to%20leverage%20those%20conversations%20to%20help%20you%20build%20a%20strategy%20or%20to%20help%20you%20build%20messaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20we%20have%20automated%20gestures%2C%20I%20often%20give%20a%20thumbs%20up%20at%20very%20inappropriate%20times%20because%20I'm%20a%20very%20hand-gesturing%20person.%20Sometimes%20I'll%20do%20a%20hand%20gesture%2C%20and%20the%20next%20thing%20you%20know%2C%20I've%20got%20a%20thumbs%20up%20flying%20across%20the%20screen.%20So%20that's%20my%20typical%20go-to%20embarrassing%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-cmo-talks-about-how-the-brand-campaign%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774712163000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6e0dff573a637a7567051%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-cmo-talks-about-how-the-brand-campaign%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kimberly%20Storin%2C%20Zoom's%20lead%20marketer%2C%20shares%20insights%20behind%20its%20ad%20campaign%20with%20Bowen%20Yang%2C%20highlighting%20user%20affinity%20for%20its%20simplicity%20and%20tools.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erica%20Iacono)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-cmo-talks-about-how-the-brand-campaign%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Losing%20one%20of%20my%20students%20led%20me%20to%20reshape%20my%20priorities%20at%20home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226150%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20classroom%20full%20of%20desks.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c536e9732a02451471360d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETK%3Cp%3EWashdog%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20an%20ordinary%20morning%20at%20the%20school%20I%20was%20teaching%20at%2C%20until%20it%20wasn't.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELosing%20a%20student%20instantly%20shifted%20my%20perspective%20on%20parenting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20ordinary%20moments%20matter%20more%2C%20and%20I'm%20trying%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20ordinary%20day.%20Until%20it%20wasn't.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschool-start-times-2016-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eschool%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20hadn't%20even%20started%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20were%20gathered%20in%20the%20auditorium%20the%20way%20they%20did%20every%20morning%20%E2%80%94%20the%20early%20arrivals%20waiting%20for%20the%20first%20bell.%20Some%20were%20half-asleep.%20Others%20were%20talking%20with%20friends%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-tech-execs-balance-ai-screentime-social-media-limits-kids-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escrolling%20their%20phones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20finishing%20homework.%20It%20was%20the%20quiet%2C%20in-between%20time%20before%20the%20day%20officially%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20suddenly%2C%20everything%20changed.%20One%20of%20my%20students%20collapsed%20right%20in%20front%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20moment%2C%20there%20was%20confusion.%20I%20was%20the%20first%20to%20reach%20her.%20Other%20teachers%20and%20staff%20rushed%20forward%20while%20the%20room%20filled%20with%20that%20strange%2C%20suspended%20silence%20that%20happens%20when%20people%20realize%20something%20is%20terribly%20wrong%20but%20don't%20yet%20understand%20what's%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmergency%20responders%20arrived.%20Students%20were%20ushered%20out.%20Adults%20moved%20quickly%2C%20trying%20to%20manage%20the%20situation%20while%20shielding%20hundreds%20of%20teenagers%20from%20a%20moment%20no%20one%20should%20have%20to%20witness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20eventually%2C%20the%20school%20day%20started%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20one%20of%20the%20unspoken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-school-teacher-now-homeschools-her-own-kids-redefine-success-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexpectations%20of%20teaching%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20the%20day%20keeps%20moving.%20Classes%20begin.%20Lessons%20continue.%20Students%20still%20need%20structure%2C%20routine%2C%20and%20stability%20%E2%80%94%20even%20when%20the%20adults%20in%20the%20room%20are%20struggling%20to%20process%20what%20just%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20that%20followed%2C%20I%20stood%20in%20front%20of%20my%20classroom%20and%20did%20what%20teachers%20do.%20I%20taught%20lessons.%20I%20answered%20questions.%20I%20graded%20assignments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20outside%2C%20it%20probably%20looked%20like%20things%20had%20returned%20to%20normal.%20Inside%2C%20something%20had%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260d5ca4e-48e7-40c8-9885-aaff6fafe90e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEverything%20changed%20for%20me%20that%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%20day%2C%20I%20carried%20the%20quiet%20assumption%20that%20many%20adults%20do%20%E2%80%94%20the%20belief%20that%20if%20you%20work%20hard%2C%20plan%20carefully%2C%20and%20follow%20the%20rules%2C%20life%20will%20mostly%20stay%20within%20the%20lines%20you've%20drawn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELosing%20a%20student%20shattered%20that%20belief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20forced%20me%20to%20confront%20a%20difficult%20truth%2C%20especially%20for%20parents%2C%20that's%20hard%20to%20sit%20with%3A%20control%20is%20mostly%20an%20illusion.%20You%20can%20supervise%2C%20plan%2C%20protect%2C%20and%20prepare.%20You%20can%20do%20everything%20right.%20And%20still%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffather-lost-his-son-harassed-online-by-anti-vaxxers-atlantic-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elife%20can%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20instant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221206%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%2C%20Nicole%20Schildt%2C%20poses%20with%20her%20daughter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c536a048461c18d7be646e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22905%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20that%20the%20experience%20of%20losing%20a%20student%20instantly%20shifted%20how%20she%20approached%20parenting%20her%20own%20children.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Nicole%20Schildt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20went%20home%20to%20my%20own%20children%20after%20that%20experience%2C%20I%20noticed%20the%20shift%20almost%20immediately.%20The%20ordinary%20moments%20felt%20different.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-evening-walk-bedtime-routine-calm-kids-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBedtime%20routines%3C%2Fa%3E%20lasted%20a%20little%20longer.%20I%20lingered%20a%20little%20more%20when%20my%20kids%20wrapped%20their%20arms%20around%20me%20before%20running%20off%20to%20school.%20Conversations%20in%20the%20car%20suddenly%20felt%20more%20important%20than%20finishing%20one%20more%20chore%20when%20we%20got%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b04200f8-9fa8-46d9-8fa6-958190bc2f8e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAchievement%20started%20to%20look%20different%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20teachers%2C%20we%20spend%20much%20of%20our%20professional%20lives%20measuring%20progress%20%E2%80%94%20grades%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-admissions-expert-teens-taking-too-many-ap-classes-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etest%20scores%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20benchmarks%2C%20performance%20data.%20As%20parents%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20carry%20that%20same%20mindset%20home.%20We%20worry%20about%20whether%20our%20kids%20are%20ahead%2C%20behind%2C%20or%20doing%20enough%20to%20keep%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20standing%20in%20a%20school%20auditorium%20after%20losing%20a%20student%20has%20a%20way%20of%20rearranging%20your%20priorities.%20I%20realized%2C%20rather%20suddenly%2C%20that%20the%20most%20important%20things%20aren't%20measurable%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20way%20your%20child%20tells%20you%20a%20long%2C%20rambling%20story%20about%20their%20day.%20The%20quick%20hug%20before%20they%20run%20out%20the%20door%20to%20play.%20The%20moments%20that%20feel%20small%20enough%20to%20rush%20past.%20Those%20are%20the%20moments%20that%20matter%2C%20and%20I'm%20paying%20more%20attention%20to%20them%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c5b1379-8da3-456f-b442-cbe3deabb3bc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ordinary%20moments%20matter%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20many%20people%20don't%20realize%20about%20teaching%20is%20that%20experiences%20like%20this%20don't%20stay%20at%20school.%20Teachers%20carry%20them%20home.%20They%20sit%20quietly%20in%20the%20background%20of%20everyday%20life%2C%20shaping%20the%20way%20we%20see%20our%20own%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20losing%20a%20student%20didn't%20just%20change%20the%20way%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-careers-from-teacher-to-virtual-assitance-work-life-balance-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esee%20the%20classroom%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20changed%20the%20way%20I%20see%20time%2C%20the%20way%20I%20parent%2C%20and%20the%20way%20I%20move%20through%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20reminded%20me%20that%20the%20ordinary%20moments%20we%20assume%20we'll%20always%20have%20are%20often%20the%20most%20fragile%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20most%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floss-reshaped-perspective-at-home-grief-parenting-focus-small-moments-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774711861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c53701299090a8c09b67ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floss-reshaped-perspective-at-home-grief-parenting-focus-small-moments-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20school%20day%20started%20like%20any%20other%2C%20then%20something%20happened%20that%20changed%20the%20way%20I%20parent%20my%20children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Nicole%20Schildt)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floss-reshaped-perspective-at-home-grief-parenting-focus-small-moments-2026-3%22%2C%22cd