r.com%2Fhow-college-freshmen-successful-first-year-professor-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20year%20of%20college%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20attended%20his%20high%20school%20basketball%20coach's%20wedding%20and%20noticed%20that%20most%20of%20his%20teammates%20were%20wearing%20bow%20ties.%20We%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20trend%2C%20but%20we%20discovered%20something%20much%20bigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20and%20I%20started%20playing%20around%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20starting%20an%20online%20bow%20tie%20business.%20Roland%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20being%20his%20own%20boss%2C%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-challenges-of-being-an-entrepreneur-from-loneliness-to-stress-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20an%20entrepreneur%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20building%20something%20for%20the%20family.%20I%20loved%20the%20idea%20of%20naming%20it%20after%20my%20father%20and%20my%20son%2C%20who%20share%20a%20name.%20I%20also%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20having%20something%20to%20keep%20us%20connected%20while%20he%20was%20away%20at%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20was%20the%20creative%20force.%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20operations%20and%20logistics.%20He%20was%20away%20at%20college%2C%20but%20we%20made%20it%20work.%20We%20were%20excited%20to%20build%20a%20legacy%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e749a856-cbc5-48de-940e-6a04da94f56a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20figured%20out%20the%20formula%20fast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-amazonbasics-private-label-brands-7-22%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20private-label%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20learning%20about%20online%20traffic%20and%20keywords%2C%20we%20quickly%20mastered%20the%20process.%20It%20came%20at%20a%20great%20time.%20Roland%20had%20transferred%20from%20a%20junior%20college%20to%20a%20private%20four-year%20HBCU.%20It%20was%20an%20exciting%20move%2C%20but%20also%20very%20expensive%2C%20with%20tuition%2C%20fees%2C%20and%20room%20and%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20would%20be%20selling%20to%20young%2C%20swaggy%20college%20students%20and%20professors.%20Then%20someone%20asked%20if%20we%20could%20make%20one%20for%20her%20pig.%20Another%20person%20asked%20for%20a%20smaller%20size%20for%20a%20woman.%20We%20began%20looking%20at%20our%20data%20to%20learn%20who%20was%20actually%20buying.%20Our%20customer%20base%20was%20broad%20and%20far%20from%20what%20we%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20was%20doing%20well%2C%20and%20the%20money%20was%20going%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fhow-to-pay-for-college%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20being%20reinvested%20in%20growth.%20We%20explored%20different%20designs%20and%20complementary%20accessories%2C%20such%20as%20socks%20and%20pins.%20But%20the%20bestseller%20remained%20our%20bow%20ties.%20The%20winning%20formula%20was%20volume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9b48b4a-cfa3-4efb-8611-26238a347991%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThen%20the%20cracks%20started%20to%20show%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20began%20looking%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-fashion-week-best-celebrity-looks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efashion%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20selling%20in%20retail.%20He%20toyed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20writing%20a%20book%20and%20creating%20a%20style%20guide.%20Social%20media%20was%20growing%2C%20and%20opportunities%20seemed%20plentiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20breaking%20point%20came%20when%20Walmart%20approached%20us%20to%20sell%20on%20Walmart.com.%20Roland%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20couture%20brand%20and%20sell%20on%20the%20runways%20of%20Fashion%20Week.%20I%20believed%20in%20the%20volume%20of%20a%20mass%20audience.%20We%20could%20not%20close%20that%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20him%20to%20be%20the%20face%20of%20the%20brand.%20He%20wanted%20to%20stay%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20I%20wanted%20to%20highlight%20one%20celebrity.%20He%20wanted%20to%20highlight%20another.%20Our%20differences%20were%20slowing%20us%20down.%20My%20son%20and%20I%20got%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-assistant-agent-in-meetings-etiquette-experts-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econference%20calls%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20disagreed%20in%20front%20of%20other%20people.%20It%20was%20awkward%20and%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wanted%20more%20control%20of%20the%20money%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20prioritize%20tuition%20and%20business%20growth.%20Soon%20he%20was%20saying%20left%2C%20and%20I%20was%20saying%20right.%20The%20arguments%20got%20tedious%2C%20and%20we%20reached%20an%20impasse.%20The%20conversations%20were%20tense.%20Holidays%20were%20not%20fun.%20Everything%20became%20a%20potential%20powder%20keg%20for%20us%20and%20anyone%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e8fb63f-f1b3-473b-af40-4f422ebe9e44%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20never%20really%20about%20the%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20we%20disagreed%20about%20money%20and%20strategy%2C%20but%20below%20the%20surface%20was%20a%20mother%20who%20needed%20additional%20income%20to%20provide%20the%20college%20experience%20I%20wanted%20for%20him%2C%20and%20a%20son%20who%20was%20learning%20to%20flex%20his%20business%20skills%20and%20his%20adult%20independence.%20It%20was%20not%20just%20money%20for%20either%20of%20us.%20It%20was%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20check%20myself%2C%20especially%20after%20watching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-succession-gets-right-about-real-life-billionaires-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSuccession%26quot%3B%20on%20HBO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Was%20I%20becoming%20Logan%20Roy%2C%20the%20controlling%20parent%20who%20made%20his%20children%20feel%20unworthy%3F%20I%20also%20thought%20about%20%26quot%3BSoul%20Food%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20had%20aired%20years%20earlier.%20That%20show%20is%20about%20family%20bonds%20under%20strain%20and%20the%20terrifying%20realization%20that%20money%2C%20pride%2C%20and%20seemingly%20reasonable%20solutions%20can%20still%20tear%20apart%20what%20matters%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20was%20trying%20to%20build%20an%20independent%20life%20while%20being%20shaped%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flived-with-grandparents-to-save-money-boundaries-changes-family-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20dynamics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20expectations.%20The%20thing%20we%20had%20built%20to%20bring%20us%20closer%20was%20starting%20to%20tear%20us%20apart.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20business%20was%20profitable%2C%20I%20had%20to%20ask%20whether%20it%20was%20actually%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245584c09-c4f6-4334-b220-a98a66b028a8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWalking%20away%20was%20the%20right%20call%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20asked%20why%20one%20of%20us%20could%20not%20simply%20run%20the%20business%20without%20the%20other.%20We%20contemplated%20that.%20But%20the%20deeper%20reality%20was%20about%20what%20the%20business%20had%20come%20to%20mean%20between%20us.%20Neither%20of%20us%20had%20the%20appetite%20to%20untangle%20it.%20It%20was%20easier%20to%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20have%20fun%20now%3A%20at%20family%20dinners%2C%20on%20holidays%2C%20and%20on%20vacations.%20We%20now%20have%20priceless%20memories%20as%20mother%20and%20son%2C%20not%20co-founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-son-built-successful-business-together-fought-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774699621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c56f2048461c18d7be66d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-son-built-successful-business-together-fought-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20built%20a%20successful%20business%20on%20Amazon%2C%20using%20the%20revenue%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20son's%20college%20tuition.%20But%20we%20couldn't%20agree%20on%20the%20company's%20direction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Andrea%20L.%20Henderson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-son-built-successful-business-together-fought-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20from%20Texas%20to%20Italy%20to%20retire.%20I'm%20saving%20over%20%2420%2C000%20a%20year%20on%20healthcare%2C%20and%20life%20is%20cheaper%20and%20calmer%20overall.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20standing%20outside%20of%20a%20building%20in%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6aa7b8e44c01630d317a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrad%20Allan%20decided%20to%20retire%20in%20Italy%20instead%20of%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brad%20Allan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBrad%20Allan%20and%20his%20wife%20moved%20to%20Montepulciano%2C%20Italy%2C%20to%20live%20out%20their%20retirement%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EItaly's%20low-cost%20healthcare%20was%20a%20big%20draw%20coming%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAllan%20said%20having%20a%20home%20base%20in%20Italy%20has%20made%20traveling%20throughout%20Europe%20easier%20and%20cheaper.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Brad%20Allan%2C%20an%20American%20who%20relocated%20from%20Austin%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20Olivia%2C%20to%20Montepulciano%2C%20Italy%2C%20to%20retire.%20Allan%2C%2060%2C%20now%20gives%20advice%20to%20other%20expats%20in%20Italy%20through%20his%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20BradsWorld.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20I%20owned%20a%20chain%20of%20furniture%20stores%20and%20dabbled%20in%20investing%20in%20multifamily%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-sold-everything-retired-in-europe-albania-pros-cons-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eretiring%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20about%20being%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20I%20had%20when%20I%20was%20running%20my%20stores%20and%20owning%20multifamily%20and%20actively%20working%20in%20the%20US.%20Without%20being%20clich%C3%A9%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20be%20able%20to%20lead%20a%20Champagne%20life%20on%20a%20beer%20budget%3B%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stretch%20our%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20online%2C%20it's%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-bought-a-cheap-house-in-italy-sicily-listings-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einexpensive%20to%20buy%20nice%20properties%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20can%20remember%20at%20least%2010%20years%20ago%20looking%20at%20real%20estate%20listings%20and%20daydreaming%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-us-for-italy-retire-in-sicily-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eretiring%20in%20Italy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Southern%20France%2C%20or%20Spain.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20big%20travelers%20%E2%80%94%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20three%20or%20four%20international%20trips%20a%20year.%20We%20went%20everywhere%2C%20but%20we%20always%20gravitated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-region-in-italy-to-visit-from-frequent-traveler-basilicata-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20Southern%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Italy%20was%20always%20on%20the%20radar.%20We%20got%20serious%20about%20it%20just%20before%20COVID.%20We%20took%20a%20six-week%20trip%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202019%2C%20and%20drove%20around%20all%20of%20Italy%20from%20the%20very%20northern%20part%20all%20the%20way%20down%20into%20the%20heel%20of%20the%20boot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224445%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20over%20the%20Tuscan%20countryside%20and%20the%20town%20of%20Montepulciano%20at%20sunset%2C%20Italy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6b7bfe99557fb1b08a0bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222964%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMontepulciano%2C%20Italy.%3Cp%3Ejenifoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ended%20up%20choosing%20to%20buy%20property%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftuscany-americans-moving-italy-cost-of-living-slow-pace-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESouthern%20Tuscany%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20specifically%20right%20on%20the%20Umbria%20border.%20The%20other%20areas%20are%20nice%2C%20but%20we%20felt%20most%20comfortable%20here%20%E2%80%94%20we%20had%20been%20here%20a%20lot%20and%20knew%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20here%20full-time%20in%202023%20and%20love%20it.%20We%20just%20felt%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20natural%20beauty%20here%20is%20otherworldly.%20We've%20found%20the%20people%20to%20be%20very%20friendly%2C%20and%20people%20always%20talk%20about%20%3Cem%3Ela%20dolce%20vita%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20life.%20Plus%2C%20we%20really%20like%20wine%2C%20and%20the%20quality%20here%20is%20second%20to%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a361b510-5e1f-4bba-b45f-c6a6570fa2a2%5C%22%3EItaly's%20healthcare%20is%20inexpensive%20compared%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20No.%201%20thing%20to%20know%20is%20that%20in%20general%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-living-in-italy-thankful-for-healthcare-for-daughter-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%20in%20Italy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20very%20inexpensive.%20Even%20if%20you're%20not%20on%20the%20national%20healthcare%20plan%2C%20you%20can%20come%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20retired%2C%20you're%20not%20having%20anybody%20paying%20into%20the%20system%20for%20you.%20So%20we%20paid%202%2C800%20euros%20%5B%3Cem%3Eabout%20%243%2C228%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20for%20our%20buy-in%20to%20the%20national%20healthcare%20system%20for%20the%20year.%20What%20was%20our%20payment%20for%20one%20month%20in%20the%20US%20pays%20our%20healthcare%20for%20the%20year%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20anything%20unless%20we%20wanted%20one%20expedited%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20my%20wife%20needed%20an%20MRI%2C%20with%20and%20without%20contrast%2C%20and%20we%20went%20to%20the%20local%20MRI%20private%20clinic%20not%20through%20the%20healthcare%20system.%20I%20believe%20it%20was%20200%20euros%20for%20two%20different%20MRIs.%20I%20had%20to%20get%20an%20X-ray%2C%20and%20it%20was%20%2430.%20A%20doctor's%20visit%20is%2050%20euros%2C%20and%20a%20specialist%20visit%20is%20120%20euros.%20So%20it's%20very%20inexpensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20woman%20taking%20a%20selfie.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6aa7be99557fb1b08a035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAllan%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Olivia.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brad%20Allan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2060%20years%20old%2C%20I'm%20still%20five%20years%20away%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-americans-on-the-brink-of-losing-health-insurance-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebeing%20able%20to%20get%20Medicare%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20my%20wife's%2015%20years%20away%20from%20that.%20So%20that's%20a%20long%20time%20when%20you're%20unemployed%20%E2%80%94%20as%20you%20are%20when%20you're%20retired%20%E2%80%94%20to%20be%20paying%20%243%2C000%20a%20month%20in%20healthcare%20costs%20in%20the%20US.%20So%20that's%20a%20huge%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20the%20taxes%20are%20so%20high%20in%20Italy.%20It's%20six%20points%20higher%20than%20the%20top%20line%20in%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%20And%20yes%2C%20the%20scale%20maxes%20out%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20US%2C%20but%20taxes%20aren't%20just%20federal%20income%20tax%3B%20it's%20also%20property%20tax%2C%20and%20I%20consider%20healthcare%20costs%20to%20be%20a%20tax%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20all%20those%20things%20together%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-florida-to-italy-cheaper-homes-better-healthcare-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EItaly%20is%20much%20more%20affordable%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20when%20you're%20retired%2C%20you're%20not%20making%20as%20much%20income.%20And%20yeah%2C%20maybe%20we%20paid%20an%20extra%20%245%2C000%20in%20federal%20tax%20here%2C%20but%20we%20saved%20%2420%2C000%20in%20property%20tax%2C%20which%20is%20what%20we%20had%20to%20pay%20in%20Texas.%20And%20we%20saved%20over%20%2420%2C000%20in%20healthcare%20costs.%20That's%20huge%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22843c051b-25d9-4124-88fe-d36134772207%5C%22%3ELiving%20in%20Europe%20is%20calmer%2C%20and%20traveling%20is%20a%20lot%20easier%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENobody%20here%20asks%20you%20what%20you%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20much%20do%20you%20make%3F%20What%20do%20you%20do%20for%20a%20living%3F%26quot%3B%20You%20don't%20get%20personal%20questions%20like%20that%2C%20which%20I%20find%20to%20be%20refreshing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moved-to-italy-new-definition-of-success-better-life-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eslower%20pace%20of%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20eat%20dinner%20so%20much%20later%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20chowing%20down%20on%20the%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20terrace%20overlooking%20the%20landscape%20in%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6aa7b445048b5f68bbae6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAllan's%20terrace%20in%20Montepulciano%2C%20Italy.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brad%20Allan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20prices%20are%20different.%20If%20you%20go%20out%20to%20dinner%20here%2C%20you'll%20be%20amazed.%20You%20go%20out%20to%20town%20here%20with%20a%20good%20bottle%20of%20wine%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20is%20a%20tourist%20town%20%E2%80%94%20and%20your%20total%20bill%20is%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20%2460%20out%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20also%20able%20to%20take%20trips%20to%20really%20interesting%20places%20with%20Italy%20as%20our%20home%20base.%20Two%20weeks%20ago%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-traveling-to-canary-islands-spain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ego%20to%20Tenerife%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20week%20because%20it%20was%20%2429%20each%20way%20to%20fly%20%E2%80%94%20of%20course%2C%20by%20the%20time%20they%20hit%20you%20with%20bags%2C%20it's%20not%20%2429%20each%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20can%20just%20hop%20on%20a%20plane%20and%20go%20to%20so%20many%20really%20unique%20places%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20issues%20with%20five-hour%20waits%20from%20TSA.%20There's%20an%20ease%20of%20getting%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20never%20take%20trains%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20when%20my%20brother-in-law's%20visiting%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20pop%20down%20to%20Naples%3B%20it's%20only%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours%20by%20train%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20like%20180%20miles%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20posing%20during%20a%20sunset%20in%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6aa7b445048b5f68bbae7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAllan's%20wife%2C%20Olivia%2C%20in%20Italy.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brad%20Allan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20we%20went%20to%20Scotland%20and%20London%20on%20two%20different%20trips.%20We%20went%20twice%20to%20the%20French%20Alps%20in%20the%20summertime%2C%20because%20it%20gets%20pretty%20warm%20here.%20We%20have%20two%20big%20dogs%2C%20and%20we%20took%20them%20French%20Alps%20so%20they%20could%20swim%20in%20the%20river.%20It's%20beautiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20drove%20to%20go%20do%20that%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20six-hour%20drive.%20And%20that's%20all%20within%20the%20last%2012%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20nice%20that%20we're%20now%20able%20to%20do%20those%20kinds%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-texas-to-italy-retire-saving-healthcare-costs-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774698361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6aa7b8e44c01630d317a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-texas-to-italy-retire-saving-healthcare-costs-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brad%20Allan%20and%20his%20wife%20moved%20from%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20to%20Italy%20to%20retire.%20They're%20saving%20over%20%2420%2C000%20on%20healthcare%20costs%2C%20and%20enjoy%20being%20able%20to%20travel%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-texas-to-italy-retire-saving-healthcare-costs-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%