%2C%20both%20experts%20agree%3A%20food%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20often%20forget%20the%20relationship%20children%20have%20with%20food%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sanchita.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20grow%20microgreens%20or%20help%20stir%20%3Cem%3Edosa%3C%2Fem%3E%20batter%2C%20they%20value%20food%20differently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandhya%20echoes%20this%2C%20drawing%20from%20Western%20practices%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20countries%2C%20children%20are%20encouraged%20to%20join%20in%20kitchens.%20Let%20them%20knead%20dough%2C%20cut%20veggies%2C%20or%20make%20pancake%20shapes.%20Even%20if%20the%20kitchen%20gets%20messy%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20more%20likely%20to%20eat%20the%20food%20they%20helped%20make.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPlanting%20seeds%20for%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildhood%20is%20fleeting%2C%20but%20its%20foundations%20last%20a%20lifetime.%20By%20the%20age%20of%20five%2C%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20brain%20is%20already%2090%25%20developed.%20The%20foods%20parents%20offer%20in%20these%20early%20years%20%E2%80%94%20say%20millet%20%3Cem%3Edosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Einstead%20of%20instant%20noodles%2C%20microgreen%20salads%20instead%20of%20fries%20%E2%80%94%20quietly%20shape%20not%20just%20health%2C%20but%20focus%2C%20mood%2C%20and%20resilience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2FAjay-growing-microgreens-in-racks-and-food-grade-trays-under-in-a-controlled-environment-1669988504.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microgreens%20in%20food%20grade%20trays%20are%20grown%20in%20controlled%20environment.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2FAjay-growing-microgreens-in-racks-and-food-grade-trays-under-in-a-controlle